{"title_page": "Credenda/Agenda", "text_new": "{{Infobox magazine|\ntitle          = Credenda/Agenda|\nimage_file = Credenda Agenda cover.jpg | image_size = 200px ||\neditor         = [[Douglas Wilson (theologian)|Douglas Wilson]] |\nfrequency      = Quarterly |\ncategory       = [[Christianity]]|\npublisher      = [[Christ Church (Moscow, Idaho)|Christ Church]]  |\nfounded      = 1988 |\ncountry        = United States |\nbased    =  Moscow, Idaho |\nlanguage       = [[English language|English]] |\nwebsite        = [http://www.credenda.org/ www.credenda.org] | \nissn           = |\noclc           = 38197050|\n}}\n\n'''''Credenda/Agenda''''' is a [[Christianity|Christian]] [[culture|cultural]] and [[theology|theological]] journal, published under the auspices of [[Christ Church (Moscow, Idaho)|Christ Church]] of [[Moscow, Idaho]]. [[Douglas Wilson (theologian)|Douglas Wilson]] serves as [[Editing|editor]], Douglas Jones as senior editor, and [[N. D. Wilson]] as [[managing editor]]. Editions are published quarterly in print form and also electronically on the [[internet]]. [[Canon Press]], another ministry of Christ Church, also produces an audio edition.\n\n''Credenda/Agenda'' began appearing in 1988 as a loose-paper pamphlet, though the format was revised in 1997 to a full-page [[magazine]]. The title is [[Latin]] for \"Things to be believed/things to be done\".\n\nPublication appears to have ended in 2012, although back issues are still for sale at the CanonPress website.<sup>[http://canonpress.com/credenda]</sup>\n\n==Subject matter==\n\nThe magazine's subject matter is typically of a [[religious]] nature, though film and book reviews, [[satire]] of prominent news stories, poems, and [[short story|short stories]] are common. Each issue has a general theme to which many of the articles relate. Past themes have included [[escapism]], [[paedocommunion]], the [[Textus Receptus]], [[sex]], [[C. S. Lewis]], [[P. G. Wodehouse]], [[cheese]] and [[Beowulf]], and special issues have addressed the [[September 11, 2001 attacks]]<sup>[https://web.archive.org/web/20041010131826/http://credenda.org/issues/13-4.php]</sup> and the editors' views on the [[New Perspective on Paul]].<sup>[https://web.archive.org/web/20040813104619/http://www.credenda.org/issues/15-5.php]</sup>\n\nThe magazine advocates a Reformed [[soteriology]], a [[liturgy|liturgical]] approach to [[worship]], a [[Cornelius Van Til|Van Tillian]] approach to [[presuppositional apologetics|apologetics]], the [[federal headship]] of men within the family, and the cultivation of the mind through the [[liberal arts]] and the [[Western culture|Western tradition]].\n\nA number of the articles from the magazine have been collected and expanded into books, including some of Douglas and Nancy Wilson's books on family life \u2014 ''Reforming Marriage'' (1995), ''Fruit of Her Hands'' (1997), ''Standing on the Promises'' (1997), ''Federal Husband'' (1999), and others \u2014 and Douglas Wilson and Douglas Jones's volume on cultural vision, ''Angels in the Architecture'' (1998).\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of theological journals]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Credenda Agenda}}\n[[Category:American quarterly magazines]]\n[[Category:Christian magazines]]\n[[Category:American cultural magazines]]\n[[Category:Magazines established in 1988]]\n[[Category:Media in Moscow, Idaho]]\n[[Category:Magazines published in Idaho]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Magazine|\ntitle          = Credenda/Agenda|\nimage_file = Credenda Agenda cover.jpg | image_size = 200px ||\neditor         = [[Douglas Wilson (theologian)|Douglas Wilson]] |\nfrequency      = Quarterly |\ncategory       = [[Christianity]]|\npublisher      = [[Christ Church (Moscow, Idaho)|Christ Church]]  |\nfounded      = 1988 |\ncountry        = United States |\nbased    =  Moscow, Idaho |\nlanguage       = [[English language|English]] |\nwebsite        = [http://www.credenda.org/ www.credenda.org] | \nissn           = |\noclc           = 38197050|\n}}\n\n'''''Credenda/Agenda''''' is a [[Christianity|Christian]] [[culture|cultural]] and [[theology|theological]] journal, published under the auspices of [[Christ Church (Moscow, Idaho)|Christ Church]] of [[Moscow, Idaho]]. [[Douglas Wilson (theologian)|Douglas Wilson]] serves as [[Editing|editor]], Douglas Jones as senior editor, and [[N. D. Wilson]] as [[managing editor]]. Editions are published quarterly in print form and also electronically on the [[internet]]. [[Canon Press]], another ministry of Christ Church, also produces an audio edition.\n\n''Credenda/Agenda'' began appearing in 1988 as a loose-paper pamphlet, though the format was revised in 1997 to a full-page [[magazine]]. The title is [[Latin]] for \"Things to be believed/things to be done\".\n\nPublication appears to have ended in 2012, although back issues are still for sale at the CanonPress website.<sup>[http://canonpress.com/credenda]</sup>\n\n==Subject matter==\n\nThe magazine's subject matter is typically of a [[religious]] nature, though film and book reviews, [[satire]] of prominent news stories, poems, and [[short story|short stories]] are common. Each issue has a general theme to which many of the articles relate. Past themes have included [[escapism]], [[paedocommunion]], the [[Textus Receptus]], [[sex]], [[C. S. Lewis]], [[P. G. Wodehouse]], [[cheese]] and [[Beowulf]], and special issues have addressed the [[September 11, 2001 attacks]]<sup>[https://web.archive.org/web/20041010131826/http://credenda.org/issues/13-4.php]</sup> and the editors' views on the [[New Perspective on Paul]].<sup>[https://web.archive.org/web/20040813104619/http://www.credenda.org/issues/15-5.php]</sup>\n\nThe magazine advocates a Reformed [[soteriology]], a [[liturgy|liturgical]] approach to [[worship]], a [[Cornelius Van Til|Van Tillian]] approach to [[presuppositional apologetics|apologetics]], the [[federal headship]] of men within the family, and the cultivation of the mind through the [[liberal arts]] and the [[Western culture|Western tradition]].\n\nA number of the articles from the magazine have been collected and expanded into books, including some of Douglas and Nancy Wilson's books on family life \u2014 ''Reforming Marriage'' (1995), ''Fruit of Her Hands'' (1997), ''Standing on the Promises'' (1997), ''Federal Husband'' (1999), and others \u2014 and Douglas Wilson and Douglas Jones's volume on cultural vision, ''Angels in the Architecture'' (1998).\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of theological journals]]\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Credenda Agenda}}\n[[Category:American quarterly magazines]]\n[[Category:Christian magazines]]\n[[Category:Cultural magazines]]\n[[Category:Magazines established in 1988]]\n[[Category:Media in Moscow, Idaho]]\n[[Category:Magazines published in Idaho]]\n", "name_user": "Hmains", "label": "safe", "comment": "category refine, sort sequence", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Credenda/Agenda"}
